  "title": "Cardiovascular physiology: Pulmonary circulation",
  "body_html": "<div>The pulmonary circulation has a special arteriolar response to hypoxia. The primary control of local blood flow is via the arterioles constricting in response to hypoxia.<br /><br />Unlike other areas of the body the pulmonary circulation does not respond to signals from the autonomic nervous system or the build up of metabolic byproducts.<br /><br /><div class='alert alert-warning'><b>Hypoxic pulmonary vasoconstriction</b> is the main regulator of pulmonary blood flow<br /></div><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti509b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti509.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><div class='imagetext'>Normal oxygenation of blood in pulmonary circulation</div><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti510b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti510.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><div class='imagetext'>Effect of hypoxic segment without hypoxic vasoconstriction response</div><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti511b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti511.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><div class='imagetext'>Hypoxic vasoconstriction results in diversion of blood away from hypoxic areas so that it may become oxygenated prior to being returned to the pulmonary veins and left atrium</div><br />As can be seen from the images above hypoxic pulmonary vasoconstriction serves to maintain ventilation-perfusion matching. <br /><br /><br /><div class='alert alert-warning'>In conditions where there is global hypoxia (e.g. lung disease or high altitude) widespread pulmonary vasoconstriction will result in increased pulmonary artery pressure and pulmonary hypertension. This may lead to right heart strain and cor pulmonale<br /></div></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"><table><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"media_link\" data-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/SJ1gu_WRx5o\" data-description=\"Hypoxic pulmonary vasoconstriction\" data-media=\"57\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"YouTube\" src=\"https://i1.ytimg.com/vi/SJ1gu_WRx5o/mqdefault.jpg\" style=\"max-width:150px;\"></a></td></tr><tr ><td style=\"padding-top:10px\" colspan=\"2\"><a style=\"\" href=\"#\" class=\"media_link\" data-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/SJ1gu_WRx5o\" data-media=\"57\">Hypoxic pulmonary vasoconstriction</a></td></tr><tr><td><span ><small>Khan academy - YouTube</small></span></td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"media_like_76\" data-mediaid=\"76\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-media btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"media_good_count_76\" class = \"media_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"media_dislike_76\" data-mediaid=\"76\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-media btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"media_bad_count_76\" class = \"media_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr></table></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">2</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcat